column5: Just a late day picture of 3 fish of many this afternoon.Took this one picture before camera battery died.lol.Sorry for the quality. Largest Pike of the day 6lb's,biggest bass 4lb's.A lot of activity for sure.
great outing on a beauty day. Congrats.
...Except for the ones on the stringer?  Nice fish.  The bass were on fire yesterday!
Lol,we kept a couple of the better ones for pictures on the stringer. All swam away for another day!!!
I am Sorry but that is odd, take a pic of te fish if you want, them let him swim.  No need for a stringer unless you are eating them.
Can you back that up bud?
Thanks guys,I'm sorry,thanks for clearing that up. believe me no harm was done. Never again.     On a side note I can't believe you guys would even question that!!!But you never know!!

I didn't comment at first, and I really don't care, but it does stress the fish out big time to be dragging them around on a stringer, and IMO there's a good chance they didn't make it, even though they may have swam away healthy.  Keep 'em next time

I caught a walleye at my cottage on the dock, put it on my stringer, fished the rest of the morning with no luck, then threw it back because I didn't feel like cleaning and cooking just one. I caught the same one less than a week later. how do I know? it had a 'soar' gill flap. Fish was handled nicely on the stringer, and obviously would have lived if he didn't get filleted the second time I caught him

And IMO,they may have. It,s nothing new to keep fish on a stringer for the day and release them. I have seen many swim away happy and healty. If your just floating around,theirs no harm,as long as they are strung right.IMO.a basket type keeper would be better.
